        "id": 193
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-06-10T01:45:33Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Actually, it seems I misremembered the lengths ip-input was validating. I wonder if we should be doing some lightweight validation there to make sure we have at least udp/tcp header worth of bytes for udp/tcp, and quickly drop broken packets.\n\nBut it could be argued that this approach is cheaper, as we compute flow hash only if lb has more than 1 bucket for \"simple\" transit packets. Let\u0027s see if any of the other consumers of the api have opinions.",
      "parentUuid": "ccf58eaf_3ecd9cd2",
      "revId": "099de5cc8955e9d67c71b1e2626777296eb1c011",
      "serverId": "6d2eb258-4fe2-443e-8a38-ca81da23d4c2"
